snippet.textDisplay:
Phil's handle is unforgettably forgettable and I have a visceral reaction each time I see it.
But yeah, anyone not in Greek Life that hangs out with people in it, know that they don't talk money in concrete terms. Which in part is due to the stigma "oh you pay for your friends." It annoys me though because financial decisions should be made fully informed. By that I mean that I've seen girls who's chapters don't have scholarships or they don't get the scholarship and then they've gone through the process for no reason. I respect Greek Life offices that state clearly the max amount a person might pay by joining one of the chapters at the uni/college. Also Greek Life is an investment, if no one bats an eye at the investment that's a house, car, or retirement plan then they also shouldn't at Greek Life dues either.
